SIMPLE: heelpost
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heelpost
<hw>Heel"post`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>The post supporting the outer end of a propeller
shaft.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Carp.)</fld> <def>The post to which a gate or door
is hinged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Engineering)</fld> <def>The quoin post of a lock
gate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heelspur</ent>⟦br⟧
